                      STAR TREK: THE ORIGINAL SERIES
                          QUICK REFERENCE GUIDE
                               FIRST SEASON


Ep#   Air Date   Prod#   Title

  1.   9/08/66    006    The Man Trap

        The Enterprise is ravaged by a creature that sucks the salt from
        its victims' bodies, and that is capable of assuming any identity.

  2.   9/15/66    008    Charlie X

        A teenager, raised by aliens and possessing some of their unusual
        powers, proves incapable of adjusting to human society and
        emotions.

  3.   9/22/66    002    Where No Man Has Gone Before

        In passing through an energy barrier at the edge of the galaxy,
        some Enterprise crew members find their ESP powers enormously
        heightened.

  4.   9/29/66    007    The Naked Time

        A strange malady strikes the crew of the Enterprise, causing them
        to succumb to their innermost desires.

  5.  10/06/66    005    The Enemy Within

        A transporter malfunction splits Kirk into two personalities, one
        brutal and incapable of control, the other gentle and incapable of
        command.

  6.  10/13/66    004    Mudd's Women

        Jack-of-all-illegal-trades Harry Mudd is transported aboard the
        Enterprise along with his cargo, three irresistibly beautiful
        women.

  7.  10/20/66    010    What Are Little Girls Made Of?

        Nurse Chapel's long-lost fiance turns up in control of a mechanism
        capable of producing android replicas of live beings.

  8.  10/27/66    012    Miri

        The landing party contracts a disease that strikes after puberty,
        while the children still alive on the planet refuse to let them
        contact the ship for help.

  9.  11/03/66    011    Dagger of the Mind

        A deranged escapee from a penal planet causes Kirk to investigate
        the psychiatric treatments being administered there.

 10.  11/10/66    003    The Corbomite Maneuver

        To stave off an attack by an alien vessel, Kirk concocts the now-
        famous "Corbomite" bluff.

 11.  11/17/66    016    The Menagerie (I)

        Spock risks the death penalty by hijacking his old commander,
        Captain Pike, to Talos IV.  Court-martial testimony recreates the
        story of Pike's earlier encounter with the Talosians.

 12.  11/24/66    016    The Menagerie (II)

        Spock risks the death penalty by hijacking his old commander,
        Captain Pike, to Talos IV.  Court-martial testimony recreates the
        story of Pike's earlier encounter with the Talosians.

 13.  12/08/66    013    The Conscience of the King

        The star of a Shakespearean acting company may be the infamous
        "Kodos the Executioner".

 14.  12/15/66    009    Balance of Terror

        Kirk matches wits against a Romulan commander in the first
        encounter between the species to occur in several decades.

 15.  12/29/66    017    Shore Leave

        The crew of the Enterprise takes shore leave on a planet where
        their every thought is immediately converted to reality.

 16.   1/05/67    014    The Galileo Seven

        Spock finds himself in command of the shuttlecraft Galileo,
        stranded on a hostile planetoid.

 17.   1/12/67    018    The Squire of Gothos

        The crew of the Enterprise are made unwilling guests of the
        powerful but capricious General Trelane (retired).

 18.   1/19/67    019    Arena

        Kirk and a reptilian alien must duel to the death to determine
        whose ship will survive.

 19.   1/26/67    021    Tomorrow Is Yesterday

        The Enterprise is accidentally flung back to the year 1967, where
        they find they must take desperate measures in an attempt to avoid
        changing history.

 20.   2/02/67    015    Court Martial

        Kirk is placed on trial when the ship's record tapes show he
        committed an error that cost a man's life.

 21.   2/09/67    022    The Return of the Archons

        An entire planet is under the total mental control of a mysterious
        being known as "Landru".

 22.   2/16/67    024    Space Seed

        The Enterprise runs across a "sleeper ship" full of supermen
        fleeing their defeat in the Eugenics Wars.

 23.   2/23/67    023    A Taste of Armageddon

        The Enterprise and its crew are declared casualties in an
        interplanetary war entirely simulated by computers.

 24.   3/02/67    025    This Side of Paradise

        Strange spores cause the entire crew of the Enterprise to mutiny
        and beam down to a planet where all work is done in unity and
        contentment.

 25.   3/09/67    026    The Devil in the Dark

        A mining operation is ravaged by a monster that dissolves men's
        bodies.

 26.   3/23/67    027    Errand of Mercy

        Kirk and Spock, stranded on Organia, attempt to interfere with the
        Klingon occupation of the planet, despite the Organians'
        insistence upon the non-necessity of violence.

 27.   3/30/67    020    The Alternative Factor

        A schizophrenic personality named Lazarus seems to be the key to
        an anomaly in the space-time fabric of the universe.

 28.   4/06/67    028    The City on the Edge of Forever

        McCoy, suffering from an overdose of cordrazine, vanishes through
        a time portal and somehow changes the past.  Kirk and Spock follow
        in an effort to rectify whatever it is that McCoy has done.

 29.   4/13/67    029    Operation: Annihilate!

        The Enterprise faces an onslaught by parasitic creatures that
        invade the nervous system to take control of their hosts.


                      STAR TREK: THE ORIGINAL SERIES
                          QUICK REFERENCE GUIDE
                              SECOND SEASON


Ep#   Air Date   Prod#   Title

 30.   9/15/67    034    Amok Time

        Spock is forced by the instinctive Vulcan mating cycle to return
        to his home planet and take a wife.

 31.   9/22/67    033    Who Mourns for Adonais?

        The Enterprise is seized by a being claiming to be the god Apollo,
        who requires their worship to survive.

 32.   9/29/67    037    The Changeling

        Nomad, an ancient Earth probe, has combined with an alien probe to
        form an incredibly powerful mechanism that is determined to
        destroy all "imperfect" life forms.

 33.  10/06/67    039    Mirror, Mirror

        Kirk, McCoy, Scott, and Uhura are accidentally exchanged with
        their counterparts in a parallel universe, where instead of the
        Federation they find a violent, dictatorial Empire.

 34.  10/13/67    038    The Apple

        The Enterprise finds itself under attack by Vaal, a machine that
        guides the actions and even the environment of a primitive
        populace.

 35.  10/20/67    035    The Doomsday Machine

        The starships Enterprise and Constellation battle an enormous
        machine that destroys planets and consumes them for fuel.

 36.  10/27/67    030    Catspaw

        Amidst an atmosphere of witches and dungeons, a pair of aliens use
        seemingly magical powers in an attempt to trick further scientific
        information from the people of the Enterprise.

 37.  11/03/67    041    I, Mudd

        The Enterprise is forced to a planet populated by androids and
        ruled by their old nemesis, Harcourt Fenton Mudd.

 38.  11/10/67    031    Metamorphosis

        A shuttlecraft is forced down to a planet as company for a
        stranded spaceman, who has been kept young by a gaseous alien
        called the "Companion".

 39.  11/17/67    044    Journey to Babel

        Crisis piles atop crisis when the Enterprise is in charge of
        transporting a volatile cargo of Federation diplomats, including
        Spock's parents.

 40.  12/01/67    032    Friday's Child

        Negotiations over mining rights become a battle for survival when
        McCoy unintentionally violates a tribal taboo.

 41.  12/08/67    040    The Deadly Years

        Kirk is relieved of command when he and other officers contract a
        disease that results in senility and death by old age within days.

 42.  12/15/67    047    Obsession

        Kirk disregards all other responsibilities in an effort to destroy
        a gaseous cloud that absorbs red corpuscles from human bodies.

 43.  12/22/67    036    Wolf in the Fold

        Scotty appears to be the only logical suspect in a bizarre series
        of murders.

 44.  12/29/67    042    The Trouble with Tribbles

        Kirk must put up with Federation bureaucrats and hordes of hungry
        tribbles while protecting a shipment of quadrotriticale against
        Klingon sabotage.

 45.   1/05/68    046    The Gamesters of Triskelion

        Kirk, Uhura, and Chekov are captured for use in gambling
        conflicts.

 46.   1/12/68    049    A Piece of the Action

        Kirk must figure out a way to counteract the effects of an earlier
        expedition, which caused a planet's civilization to pattern itself
        after the Chicago mobs of the Twenties.

 47.   1/19/68    048    The Immunity Syndrome

        A gigantic single-celled creature, which feeds on the energy
        necessary to our form of life, invades our galaxy.

 48.   2/02/68    045    A Private Little War

        When the Klingons hasten the arms development of one faction on a
        hitherto peaceful planet, Kirk must arm the other side in order to
        maintain a balance of power.

 49.   2/09/68    051    Return to Tomorrow

        Highly advanced alien minds "borrow" bodies, including those of
        Kirk and Spock, in order to build permanent android bodies. One of
        them, however, does not wish to leave his borrowed body.

 50.   2/16/68    052    Patterns of Force

        A Federation historian ignores the Prime Directive and reshapes a
        planet's society along the lines of Nazi Germany.

 51.   2/23/68    050    By Any Other Name

        A group of aliens from the Andromeda galaxy commandeer the
        Enterprise to make the journey back home.

 52.   3/01/68    065    The Omega Glory

        Captain Tracy, believing he has found a planet containing the
        secret of eternal youth, interferes in the struggle between the
        two planetary cultures, the Yangs and the Kohms.

 53.   3/08/68    053    The Ultimate Computer

        The Enterprise is put under total control of a new type of
        computer, which then refuses to relinquish control.

 54.   3/15/68    043    Bread and Circuses

        The Enterprise encounters a civilization that combines the
        features of the Roman Empire with 20th-century technology.

 55.   3/29/68    055    Assignment: Earth

        On a historical fact-finding mission to 1969, the Enterprise
        accidentally intercepts an interplanetary agent out to sabotage an
        orbiting nuclear platform.


                      STAR TREK: THE ORIGINAL SERIES
                          QUICK REFERENCE GUIDE
                               THIRD SEASON


Ep#   Air Date   Prod#   Title

 56.   9/20/68    061    Spock's Brain

        A mysterious woman surgically removes Spock's brain.

 57.   9/27/68    059    The Enterprise Incident

        Kirk goes mad and Spock turns traitor in an attempt to steal an
        improved cloaking device from the Romulans.

 58.  10/04/68    058    The Paradise Syndrome

        In a state of amnesia, Kirk marries and finds happiness with
        Miramanee, an Indian maiden.  Meanwhile, Spock must find a way to
        save her planet from an impending meteor collision.

 59.  10/11/68    060    And the Children Shall Lead

        A group of children, under alien domination, play on the crew
        members' secret fears in order to gain control of the ship.

 60.  10/18/68    062    Is There in Truth No Beauty?

        Miranda, a telepath, is jealous of Spock's greater abilities in
        forming a mind-link with Kollos, an alien so ugly that the very
        sight of him can drive a man insane.

 61.  10/25/68    056    Spectre of the Gun

        Kirk et al. find themselves on the losing side of the gunfight at
        the OK Corral.

 62.  11/01/68    066    Day of the Dove

        Klingons and the Enterprise crew must unite to overcome an alien
        who feeds on the hatred between them.

 63.  11/08/68    065    For the World Is Hollow and I Have Touched the Sk

        McCoy, suffering from a fatal disease, finds himself romantically
        entangled with the priestess governing a planetoid/spaceship on a
        collision course with another planet.

 64.  11/15/68    064    The Tholian Web

        The Tholians entrap the Enterprise, not believing that the crew is
        merely trying to save Kirk from a hyperspace warp.

 65.  11/22/68    067    Plato's Stepchildren

        The dwarf Alexander's lack of mind-over-matter abilities may be
        the only clue to aid Kirk in defeating a band of telekinetics.

 66.  11/29/68    068    Wink of an Eye

        The Enterprise is invaded by beings who move too fast for human
        eyes to detect.

 67.  12/06/68    063    The Empath

        Kirk, Spock, and McCoy are manipulated by aliens who use them to
        teach compassion to a girl capable of absorbing the pain and
        injuries of others.

 68.  12/20/68    057    Elaan of Troyius

        The Enterprise's task of transporting an imperious woman to
        another planet for marriage is complicated by Kirk's falling in
        love with her.

 69.   1/03/69    071    Whom Gods Destroy

        Captain Garth, having taken over the penal planet where he was
        being treated, uses his ability to change shape in an attempt to
        get aboard the Enterprise.

 70.   1/10/69    070    Let That Be Your Last Battlefield

        Two two-toned beings try to get Kirk to take sides in their racial
        disputes.

 71.   1/17/69    072    The Mark of Gideon

        Kirk is decoyed into a replica of the Enterprise.  While Spock
        searches for him through a maze of diplomatic red tape, the people
        of Gideon are using him as a source of alien infection.

 72.   1/24/69    069    That Which Survives

        A mysterious woman whose touch is death threatens the landing
        party.

 73.   1/31/69    073    The Lights of Zetar

        An electrical cloud formed by the life-essences of the long-dead
        Zetarians seeks to possess the body of Scotty's new-found
        sweetheart.

 74.   2/14/69    076    Requiem for Methuselah

        Flint, an immortal, uses Kirk to rouse emotions in an android, so
        that she will become fully human and can be a suitable, immortal
        mate.

 75.   2/21/69    075    The Way to Eden

        A group of space hippies are searching for the legendary planet of
        Eden.

 76.   2/28/69    074    The Cloud Minders

        Kirk's attempt to pick up a shipment of a vital mineral embroils
        him in the demands of the oppressed miners against the rulers.

 77.   3/07/69    077    The Savage Curtain

        Lincoln of Earth and Surak of Vulcan join Kirk and Spock in battle
        against a group of villains, while alien observers examine the
        distinctions between good and evil.

 78.   3/14/69    078    All Our Yesterdays

        A rescue mission to a planet whose sun is about to nova results in
        Kirk, Spock, and McCoy being sent to various eras in the planet's
        past.

 79.   6/03/69    079    Turnabout Intruder

        A woman bitterly jealous of Kirk uses an alien device to exchange
        her consciousness with his, and then attempts to kill her body and
        thus Kirk's mind.

